Rating: 0
This is a great recipe! I have used the serrano and I have used jalepeno, both were good. I used roasted green chile from Hatch, NM. All good. I did add some chiffonade cilantro to the salsa a few times and we like it very much. I have once used a can of gold pineapple chunks I coarse chopped with okay results, but fresh ripe pineapple is key to this salsa/recipe. Fresh lime juice is too. Here is a taste treat: Add about two minced/pulverized cloves of garlic, and a tablespoon of ground cumin seed to a cup of olive oil, or even corn oil, and shake well, let it sit in the refrigerator for up to a month. Then, brush on meats and poultry for an amazing flavor.

