This recipe was just ok. There are only two of us, so we made it twice this week to use up ingredients. Made it exactly as the recipe called for (liked the cumin on the chops). The first time was pretty good, but we thought of a few changes: add another fruit (like mango or payaya) to the salsa - it's just too one-dimensional (which is strange, because it shouldn't be) for us. The second change is to really dice the pineapple smaller (and maybe even mash a bit) because it sort of falls off the pork chop. It still didn't really do much for me, even the second round (although we hadn't added the second fruit.) Epicurious has so many fabulous recipes that I just don't think it's worth it to make this one again. Not that it was bad, it just was ok.

